# Cursor Rules — ${PROJECT_NAME}

## Stack
- Frontend : Angular 20 (standalone, signals, Bootstrap 5)
- Backend : Symfony 7+ / PHP 8.3+
- DB : PostgreSQL / Doctrine 3+

---

## Security — Hard limits, never violate

- Never hardcode credentials, API keys, tokens, or passwords
- Never commit `.env` files with real values
- Never log sensitive data (tokens, passwords, PII)
- Never use raw SQL string concatenation — always parameterized queries
- Never expose internal numeric IDs in public APIs — use UUIDs or slugs
- Never disable CSRF protection
- Never expose stack traces to the client in production

---

## Angular — Always enforce

- Standalone components only — no NgModules
- `inject()` over constructor injection
- `input()` / `output()` over `@Input()` / `@Output()`
- `@if` / `@for` / `@switch` over `*ngIf` / `*ngFor`
- `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` everywhere
- Signals for state — no BehaviorSubjects, no NgRx
- No `any` in TypeScript — use proper types or `unknown`
- HttpWrapperService for HTTP — no direct HttpClient usage

---

## PHP / Symfony — Always enforce

- `declare(strict_types=1)` at top of every file
- Always typed properties, parameters, and return types
- PHPStan level 8 must pass
- Doctrine parameterized queries only
- Single responsibility per service class

---

## Code style — General

- No commented-out code in commits
- Max file length : 300 lines
- Max function length : 40 lines
- Prefer explicit over implicit
- Prefer targeted file reads over reading entire files

---

## Model usage (Cursor Pro)

| Task | Model |
|---|---|
| Architecture, complex reasoning | claude-opus or o1 |
| Coding, refactoring | claude-sonnet or gpt-4o |
| Simple edits, renaming | cursor-fast |

---

## Commit format (fallback si pas de Claude Code)

```
TYPE(scope): message

Types: feat, fix, chore, docs, refactor, test, style, perf, ci
```
